Area of triangle
    area = 0.5 * base * height

Size of triangle's incenter
    incenter = perimeter / 2

https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Trigonometry/Proof:_Heron's_Formula
Heron's Formula (Area of triangle)
    triangle area = squareroot(s * (s - a) * (s - b) * (s - c))
        Where
        a, b, c = Triangle side length
        s = semi-perimeter

http://mathworld.wolfram.com/Incenter.html
http://www.mathopenref.com/coordincenter.html
Coordinates of the incenter
    xCoord = (BC*xa + AC*xb + AB*xc)/P 
    yCoord = (BC*ya + AC*yb + AB*yc)/P
        Where
        AB, AC, BC = Triangle side Length
        P = perimeter (a+b+c), 
        xa, xb, xc = x coordinate of the vertex
        ya, yb, yc = y coordinate of the vertex

http://mathworld.wolfram.com/Incircle.html
Radius of incircle
    Radius = Area / Semi-perimeter

http://mathworld.wolfram.com/Incircle.html
Area of triangle
    Area = Semi-perimeter * Radius

Circumcenter radius
    radius = (AB * AC * BC) / (4 * area)

Triangle check
To check if three sides can form a triangle,
   a + b > c && a + c > b && b + c > a
or if sorted
    a + b > c

https://www.mathsisfun.com/algebra/trig-cosine-law.html
Cosine formula
To get the third side:
    C^2 = A^2 + B^2 - 2*A*B*cos(theta)
To get the angle theta:
    theta = acos((A^2 + B^2 - C^2)/(2 * A * B))
        Where
        theta = angle between sides A and B

Law of sines
    A/sin(oppA) = B/sin(oppB) = C/sin(oppC) = 2 * circumcircleRadius

Pythagoran Theorem
    A^2 + B^2 = C^2
